<div class="container">
    <main class="row">
        <picture style="padding: 0;" class="col-lg">
            <% images.forEach(image => { %>
                <img class="img-fluid" style="width: 16%; max-height: 6em; margin: 1%; padding: 0%;"
                     src="images/skills/<%= image %>">
            <% }) %>
        </picture>
        <article class="col-lg">
            <h1 class="text-center mt-5 mb-3">A trove of knowledge</h1>
            <p>One thing is clear: I'm passionate about IT. I find the endless pool of programming languages and tools
                that exist in our day and age simply marvelous. It's impossible to master everything, but so far
                I've focused a big chunk of my efforts on <strong class="text-success">Node.js</strong>. You can
                do so much with <strong class="text-success">Node.js</strong> and its myriad of packages through
                <strong class="text-danger">npm</strong> ! 
            </p>
        </article>
    </main>
</div>

<script>
    document.querySelector("#nav-skills").classList.add("active");
</script>